<p style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 12px;"><span style="color: #c90431; font-size: 22px;">Let us show you how to make your messages easier to read and understand. Give us just <a style="color: #c90431;" href="https://corpapp.honeywell.com/sites/honvideo/Pages/Player.aspx?bctid=4897750139001&amp;UsrId=e045068&amp;ItmId=6047" target="_blank">60-seconds</a> of your time.</span> <br /></p>
<p style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 12px;">It may feel impossible to fit all of your ideas into a short, meaningful sentence. So when you&rsquo;re faced with a sentence that is clearly juggling too many ideas, try breaking it up into shorter ones.</p>
<p style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 4px;">Each sentence should have one simple thought. More than that creates <em>complexity</em> and invites <em>confusion</em>.<br /><br /></p>
